data.title: What was the Ilyas Shahi dynasty like in Medieval Bangladesh in 1342-1487 A.D.?
data.meta_description: Answer (1 of 4): Iliyas Shah (1342-1358) founder of the Iliyas Shahi dynasty. He consolidated the independent Sultanate of Bengal. liyas Shah was an inhabitant of Sijisthan, a country of east -Persia and came from a noble family. His father's name was Sultan.
